Module Paint3001

Package paint

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Action
    Sets graphics context and instruction
    FillColourPicker
    Creates a colour picker that allows the user to select a fill colour
    GUI
    Sets all GUI components and containers, sets scene, window, event handlers, styles, and option functionality
    Main
    Starts the program and launches the GUI window
    PaintButton
    Extends Button to create a button that allows the user to choose the drawing tool shape
    PaintCanvas
    Extends Canvas to create a square-shaped canvas that is resizable, along with a undo stack GUI component that updates
    PaintEllipse
    Extends Shape to draw an ellipse on to the graphics context of the canvas
    PaintLine
    Extends Shape to draw a line on to the graphics context of the canvas
    PaintPlot
    Extends Shape to draw a dot on to the graphics context of the canvas
    PaintPolygon
    Extends Shape to draw a polygon on to the graphics context of the canvas
    PaintRectangle
    Extends Shape to draw a rectangle on to the graphics context of the canvas
    PenColourPicker
    Creates a colour picker that allows the user to select a pen colour
    Read
    Reads contents of file path and outputs instructions to Canvas
    RedoButton
    Extends Button to redo an action on the canvas upon click
    SetFill
    Extends Action to set the fill colour to the specified colour, and prints the instruction of that action
    SetPen
    Extends Action to set the pen colour to the specified colour, and prints the instruction of that action
    Shape
    Extends Action to create new shape, gets and checks coordinates of the shape
    UndoButton
    Extends Button to undo an action on the canvas upon click
    UndoHistoryListView<String>
    Extends ListView to update the view with specified actions and gets the index of that action
    ViewActionsButton
    Extends Button to render specified actions on a temp canvas based on the item selected in the undo history list
    Write
    Creates a .vec file that is output to the specified file path
